This was a 1 day creation made a few weeks ago for the Xmas mapping competition, didn't really place too much thought into a layout or style other than playing some more with Cel shaded effects on custom models.

The layout is similar to several AWP maps but that was not really my intention for gameplay, just straight up GunGame action as per usual.

I've spent another day on the map to include some new snowflake effects and basic soundscape along with one interesting little thing people will discover really quickly when they play the map.

Several custom models were used in this map, they will be made available on this site in a simple to download form shortly, just need to package them up nicely is all.

personal assessment of the map, between a 5-6 perhaps, due to the requirements of the contest and just simplicity seen in the map. Nothing really stands out.

BSP Filesize: 4.88 MB Compiled for CS:S

This wasn't a horribly serious attempt at a map, just an absent minded creation for simple relaxation one day. If someone wants to go nuts with it just ask me for the .vmf and I can send it or upload it to the MiP's section even.

Enjoy and Happy Holidays, Logan Dougall

This map has been in the works for a while.  It uses a new spawn placement scheme (vertical difference vs. opposing sides) which makes play a bit more vertically oriented.

This map also makes extensive use of func_detail brushes to speed up high-quality vis rendering.  This map rendered in 'normal' vis in under 30 seconds because of the optimizations I've made.

It may be required that qubemaps be built using 'buildcubemaps' in the console, but I am pretty sure I got em working already, I'm kinda new to getting bumpmaps and cubemaps to actually work properly.

All in all, I designed this map to run fast, with plenty of players.

This is the first map I've made since the network reformat when i lost all of my other work.  The basic idea of the map is to make the ground level relatively safe with a lot of cover, but as you move up vertically on the map you can see more and more of it but you have almost no cover when on the catwalks and even less on the spider's legs.

This is a map I put together in about two days. It features breakable crates (most of them), strategic firing lanes, and great scenery (you should have seen how many env_cubemaps I stuffed in this map to make it look that much better). Even though it took me only 2 days to make, I did not skip any details, I was probably done with the layout of the map in half a day and the rest of the time was spent on putting the details into the map (snow displacements everywhere, fogging effects around the water, lighting effects, snowflakes falling...). I hope you enjoy playing this map as much as I did making it.
Just unzip it in your maps folder!

This one took a while.  The rotor blades (both nacelles and tail rotor) all spin.  Both teams have deck houses and start the round below decks.  Center area between spawns designed for fast CQB.  Airbag area/catwalks designed for long range attacks.

I hope you all like it. This is my second map I ever made. It was made for gun mod, but can be used as a fy map also. If you have any comment please send me a e-mail which is included in the text file.

Thank You & Enjoy.

Yet another map from me. This map has nothing really special but the orange / gray line in the middle wich changes the colors to opposite of what it was.

Also, the gateway on the 'bridge' has a illusionary part in the middle as a vision blocker.

Map has 56 spawns if I correctly remember; 28T & 28CT.


Also this map has an HDR effect enabled, so don't forget to enable bloom effect for some nice gloomy visuals of the map!

It seriously doesn't mean a map ain't good if it didn't take 10 days to make.
This, ( Don't take this as anything like cocky etc. ) is one of the examples. It took me ~4 hours to make, and it ain't a bad map. It has a unique design and nice lighting and not too complex playability.

I also added the HDR effect for your you, so if your computer can handle it enable bloom!

I will be maybe soon submitting another map for this particular gamemode, but the problem is I can't get it compiled because it is on my other computer and the computer crashes when I try to compile.

Have fun playing this map, and don't take the game too seriously!

This map is a modification of the original GoldSrc 2Fort from Team Fortress Classic, retextured and modified for gun game. It is only the bridge and the 2 forts.

Due to my converting the GoldSrc version of the map to a Source-compatible .vmf there are quite a few small leaks in some of the brushes, a lot I have fixed. Nothing bad and not too noticeable unless you look for them. I will try to fix some of these in future updates.


Update Notes:

V2:
- Fixed some light leaks (My benefit, to optimize compile time)
- Made part of the bridge breakable.
- Added water into the pit to avoid fall damage.
- Added lights in the sniper towers.
- Added a secret room.

V3:
- Fixed more light leaks (My benefit, to optimize compile time)
- Fixed breakable bridge.
- Made light fixtures for the lights in the forts.
- Adjusted the ladders to a slight angle.

To Do:
- Make the breakable bridge brush more complex.
- Fix most, if not all light leaks.
- Fix brush glitches.
- Make map HDR (Not until all light leaks are fixed).
- Fix brush alignment/blends.

Final notes: It seems like every time I fix one thing, 2 more problems pop up.
